just_use trick.go

# label: TINY
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Declares the Trick + Play interfaces that every trick in this package
implements. Plugin shape: stateless singleton trick (zero-sized struct),
FindPlays returns concrete Plays, each Play carries its own captured
state (no closures) and knows how to Apply against a board.

**Divergence from TS:** TS's apply(board) mutates in place and returns
the hand cards. Go returns (newBoard, played) — simpler, avoids TS's
defensive "re-check at apply time" rescan.
